After a long while, these percentages will start to stabilize. Meaning that even if the Random Surfer carries on surfing the percentages won't change much, if at all.

At this point, we can stop the algorithm running, let the Random Surfer go and use these percentages to rank the websites by importance.

Doing this is real life would take a long time and possibly result in a severe case of RSI. But luckily this process can be simulated inside Google's super computers, meaning that the whole internet can be ranked according to every conceivable search term in no time at all.

